1
00:00:29,833 --> 00:00:30,833
Me first!

2
00:00:34,416 --> 00:00:35,290
Give it!

3
00:00:35,291 --> 00:00:37,875
Oh, nice. Lovely.

4
00:00:39,375 --> 00:00:41,375
<i>Once upon a time...</i>

5
00:00:43,416 --> 00:00:46,708
<i>...there were two terrible twits.</i>

6
00:00:54,708 --> 00:00:57,416
<i>And this is how they were left for dead.</i>

7
00:00:59,708 --> 00:01:02,791
<i>Wait, wait, wait. Stop!</i>

8
00:01:04,750 --> 00:01:05,582
Mum,

9
00:01:05,583 --> 00:01:09,499
are you actually starting my bedtime story
with the characters dying?

10
00:01:09,500 --> 00:01:12,915
I didn't say they were dying.
I said they were left for dead.

11
00:01:12,916 --> 00:01:14,207
- By who?
- By whom?

12
00:01:14,208 --> 00:01:17,249
- By whom?
- Children and a family of magical animals.

13
00:01:17,250 --> 00:01:18,416
Oh.

14
00:01:19,375 --> 00:01:21,207
What kind of story is this?

15
00:01:21,208 --> 00:01:22,374
You keep telling me

16
00:01:22,375 --> 00:01:25,707
you want your bedtime stories
to be more emotionally complex

17
00:01:25,708 --> 00:01:29,665
with, I'm quoting,
"highbrow themes and lowbrow comedy."

18
00:01:29,666 --> 00:01:33,207
True. I just don't want
a boring, old, normal story.

19
00:01:33,208 --> 00:01:38,582
Well, I can assure you, my love,
this is no "normal story"

20
00:01:38,583 --> 00:01:41,875
because the Twits are not normal people.

21
00:01:43,458 --> 00:01:46,915
<i>No, the Twits hate everything,</i>

22
00:01:46,916 --> 00:01:48,915
<i>especially each other.</i>

23
00:01:48,916 --> 00:01:52,458
<i>They've been married
for 47 miserable years.</i>

24
00:01:54,416 --> 00:01:59,208
<i>And not a day has passed
without a mean, dirty trick.</i>

25
00:02:04,708 --> 00:02:09,957
<i>The thing is, even people
who hate everything love something.</i>

26
00:02:09,958 --> 00:02:15,750
<i>For the Twits, it was a backyard
amusement park called Twitlandia.</i>

27
00:02:16,875 --> 00:02:19,624
<i>They built Twitlandia from the ground up.</i>

28
00:02:19,625 --> 00:02:22,290
<i>It was the one thing
that brought them joy.</i>

29
00:02:22,291 --> 00:02:25,249
<i>The one thing they truly cared about.</i>

30
00:02:25,250 --> 00:02:28,833
<i>The one thing
they wanted the whole world to see.</i>

31
00:02:35,416 --> 00:02:38,082
<i>There's a song And dance extravaganza</i>

32
00:02:38,083 --> 00:02:40,833
<i>And rides made out of toilets</i>

33
00:02:41,416 --> 00:02:43,207
<i>This is Twitlandia!</i>

34
00:02:43,208 --> 00:02:46,040
<i>It's the world's only amusement park.</i>

35
00:02:46,041 --> 00:02:49,125
<i>And even if the whole world didn't see it,</i>

36
00:02:49,625 --> 00:02:51,665
<i>the true heroes of our story,</i>

37
00:02:51,666 --> 00:02:53,415
<i>an orphan named Beesha...</i>

38
00:02:53,416 --> 00:02:54,374
Wow.

39
00:02:54,375 --> 00:02:56,499
<i>...and her best friend, Bubsy...</i>

40
00:02:56,500 --> 00:02:57,665
Whoa!

41
00:02:57,666 --> 00:02:58,582
<i>...did.</i>

42
00:02:58,583 --> 00:03:01,624
<i>Come to Twitlandia's
grand opening this week.</i>

43
00:03:01,625 --> 00:03:04,915
- That looks like the most...
- Amazing place in the world?!

44
00:03:04,916 --> 00:03:08,499
I definitely wasn't gonna say
"horrifying and lame."

45
00:03:08,500 --> 00:03:11,999
But, Beesha,
it has a song-and-dance extravaganza

46
00:03:12,000 --> 00:03:14,082
and rides made out of toilets!

47
00:03:14,083 --> 00:03:17,499
And who doesn't want both of those things?

48
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:21,540
All right, Bubsy boy,
I promise I'll take you to Twitlandia

49
00:03:21,541 --> 00:03:25,374
before you leave me forever next week.

50
00:03:25,375 --> 00:03:27,040
Whoo-hoo!

51
00:03:27,041 --> 00:03:28,541
Twitlandia!

52
00:03:32,583 --> 00:03:34,415
Oh, Jim.

53
00:03:34,416 --> 00:03:35,457
Ah!

54
00:03:35,458 --> 00:03:37,832
Look, it's our first visitor!

55
00:03:37,833 --> 00:03:40,999
<i>But before Beesha
could fulfill her promise to Bubsy...</i>

56
00:03:41,000 --> 00:03:42,957
Welcome to Twitlandia.

57
00:03:42,958 --> 00:03:44,332
Ahem.

58
00:03:44,333 --> 00:03:46,999
Hey! You can't go in without paying!

59
00:03:47,000 --> 00:03:49,957
<i>...in fact, before the park even opened...</i>

60
00:03:49,958 --> 00:03:51,582
"Condem-ned"?

61
00:03:51,583 --> 00:03:54,040
<i>...the city shut Twitlandia down...</i>

62
00:03:54,041 --> 00:03:56,000
What's this?

63
00:03:56,500 --> 00:04:00,707
<i>...condemning it for being dangerous,
structurally unsound, and, quote...</i>

64
00:04:00,708 --> 00:04:03,916
"Stinking of rancid hot dog meat"?

65
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:06,332
- Oh, Jim!
- Huh?

66
00:04:06,333 --> 00:04:10,041
The city's...
They're shutting down our fun park!

67
00:04:11,375 --> 00:04:12,540
No...

68
00:04:12,541 --> 00:04:15,125
No!

69
00:04:22,083 --> 00:04:24,749
It was as if their baby
had been taken from them.

70
00:04:24,750 --> 00:04:26,124
Strange baby.

71
00:04:26,125 --> 00:04:27,290
Strange people.

72
00:04:27,291 --> 00:04:30,207
I do like Beesha and Bubsy
quite a bit, though.

73
00:04:30,208 --> 00:04:35,665
Yes, well, Beesha and Bubsy
are on a collision course with the Twits,

74
00:04:35,666 --> 00:04:39,124
who are about to play
their dirtiest trick yet.

75
00:04:39,125 --> 00:04:41,832
A prank that will condemn the city

76
00:04:41,833 --> 00:04:44,790
the way the city condemned Twitlandia.

77
00:04:44,791 --> 00:04:47,957
What are they gonna do?
Make it stink of rotten hot dog meat?

78
00:04:47,958 --> 00:04:51,957
Clever boy. Now, no more questions.
Just listen to the song.

79
00:04:51,958 --> 00:04:53,749
Oh, is this a musical?

80
00:04:53,750 --> 00:04:56,707
Of course it's not a musical.
What am I, a cricket?

81
00:04:56,708 --> 00:04:59,124
It's one song. Settle down.

82
00:04:59,125 --> 00:05:01,290
Bubsy goodbye video, take one.

83
00:05:01,291 --> 00:05:02,665
And... action!

84
00:05:02,666 --> 00:05:04,707
We'll miss you, Bubsy!

85
00:05:04,708 --> 00:05:06,832
Bye, Bubsy.

86
00:05:06,833 --> 00:05:12,833
<i>I look around at all these people</i>

87
00:05:14,208 --> 00:05:20,040
<i>Nice people with their perfect lives</i>

88
00:05:20,041 --> 00:05:23,499
<i>Well, they're bored
Out of their skulls</i>

89
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:24,874
Vote for John-John.

90
00:05:24,875 --> 00:05:27,166
<i>Monotonous and dull</i>

91
00:05:28,458 --> 00:05:30,457
<i>They do not live</i>

92
00:05:30,458 --> 00:05:35,082
<i>They just survive</i>

93
00:05:35,083 --> 00:05:38,915
<i>Now, we are not like Everyone else</i>

94
00:05:38,916 --> 00:05:42,040
<i>There's nobody here
That's like you and me</i>

95
00:05:42,041 --> 00:05:45,624
<i>We're one of a kind
And deep down inside</i>

96
00:05:45,625 --> 00:05:48,999
<i>We're the only ones out here</i>

97
00:05:49,000 --> 00:05:53,416
<i>Who are free</i>

98
00:05:55,083 --> 00:05:56,707
I think we're set.

99
00:05:56,708 --> 00:05:59,832
All right, Bubsy boy,
the big day's coming up.

100
00:05:59,833 --> 00:06:04,124
Hit me with your favorite memory
from the Triperot Home for Children.

101
00:06:04,125 --> 00:06:07,040
Oh! That time I got
a potato stuck in my nose?

102
00:06:07,041 --> 00:06:10,332
- Okay...
- Don't you remember, Beesh?

103
00:06:10,333 --> 00:06:12,832
You made me laugh so hard that I snorted,

104
00:06:12,833 --> 00:06:15,665
and the potato shot out,
and it landed in your milk.

105
00:06:15,666 --> 00:06:18,832
And now I'm lactose intolerant by choice.

106
00:06:18,833 --> 00:06:21,790
Okay, Harold.

107
00:06:21,791 --> 00:06:25,374
Bubsy gets adopted next week.
How do you want him to remember you?

108
00:06:25,375 --> 00:06:26,790
I...

109
00:06:26,791 --> 00:06:28,582
I... I kept the potato.

110
00:06:28,583 --> 00:06:31,874
He kept the potato. Cool.

111
00:06:31,875 --> 00:06:37,916
<i>I promise to always surprise you</i>

112
00:06:39,666 --> 00:06:44,583
<i>I promise to always be fun</i>

113
00:06:45,833 --> 00:06:49,874
<i>To be bad to the bone</i>

114
00:06:49,875 --> 00:06:52,750
<i>And you can tell everyone</i>

115
00:06:53,541 --> 00:06:59,583
<i>That I won't stop Until I'm done</i>

116
00:07:00,625 --> 00:07:03,374
<i>We're not like everyone else</i>

117
00:07:03,375 --> 00:07:07,040
<i>There's nobody here
Just like you and me</i>

118
00:07:07,041 --> 00:07:10,457
<i>We're one of a kind
And deep down inside</i>

119
00:07:10,458 --> 00:07:14,165
<i>We're the only ones out here</i>

120
00:07:14,166 --> 00:07:17,749
<i>Who are free</i>

121
00:07:17,750 --> 00:07:21,124
<i>We're the only ones out here</i>

122
00:07:21,125 --> 00:07:28,000
<i>Who are free</i>

123
00:07:38,041 --> 00:07:39,124
Okay, my turn.

124
00:07:39,125 --> 00:07:43,499
So, Bubs, I'm gonna miss
your world-class dancing,

125
00:07:43,500 --> 00:07:46,540
and I'll miss getting
your basketball unstuck

126
00:07:46,541 --> 00:07:48,832
when you throw it in the rafters.

127
00:07:48,833 --> 00:07:52,624
I'll miss tucking you in at night,
and, I don't know,

128
00:07:52,625 --> 00:07:54,790
just watching you grow up

129
00:07:54,791 --> 00:07:58,458
because you're such
a cute little squishy-wishy baby.

130
00:08:00,708 --> 00:08:01,875
What the...

131
00:08:09,125 --> 00:08:10,040
Mr. Napkin!

132
00:08:10,041 --> 00:08:11,583
Help me!

133
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,415
Mr. Napkin! Beesha!

134
00:08:31,416 --> 00:08:32,832
Are you okay?

135
00:08:32,833 --> 00:08:34,874
We're fine, Bubs. We're fine.

136
00:08:34,875 --> 00:08:37,333
What even is that stuff?

137
00:08:38,083 --> 00:08:41,040
I think it's that gross liquid meat
they use to make hot dogs.

138
00:08:41,041 --> 00:08:44,457
Yeah, it's hot dog meat, all right.
The good stuff too.

139
00:08:44,458 --> 00:08:46,082
Well, whatever it is,

140
00:08:46,083 --> 00:08:48,624
I'm glad you didn't drown in it,
Mr. Napkin.

141
00:08:48,625 --> 00:08:53,332
Oh jeez, I forgot to thank you
for saving my life, Beesha.

142
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:56,707
You know, my mom always told me
I was an ungrateful child

143
00:08:56,708 --> 00:08:59,582
and our family's biggest disappointment.

144
00:08:59,583 --> 00:09:01,332
Anyhow, thank you.

145
00:09:01,333 --> 00:09:02,374
Of course.

146
00:09:02,375 --> 00:09:05,250
The world's a much better place
with you in it, Mr. N.

147
00:09:07,083 --> 00:09:09,832
<i>Shock and outrage in Triperot today</i>

148
00:09:09,833 --> 00:09:14,249
<i>as one of the worst liquid hot dog meat
floods in the nation's history</i>

149
00:09:14,250 --> 00:09:15,749
<i>has citizens reeling.</i>

150
00:09:15,750 --> 00:09:19,207
Oi! Woman! Our prank's on telly!

151
00:09:19,208 --> 00:09:23,540
<i>When I was a little shaver,
Triperot was the fun capital of the world.</i>

152
00:09:23,541 --> 00:09:24,790
<i>We had fun.</i>

153
00:09:24,791 --> 00:09:28,415
<i>Then Tripe Lake dried up,
and I thought things couldn't get worse.</i>

154
00:09:28,416 --> 00:09:31,082
<i>Guess what? News flash. This is way worse.</i>

155
00:09:31,083 --> 00:09:32,415
<i>This is worse.</i>

156
00:09:32,416 --> 00:09:34,165
<i>What I wanna know is,</i>

157
00:09:34,166 --> 00:09:37,999
<i>how the heck can hard-working people
like us get ahead in this town?</i>

158
00:09:38,000 --> 00:09:40,249
<i>I also wanna know that, also as well.</i>

159
00:09:40,250 --> 00:09:41,665
<i>I'm Beverly Onion,</i>

160
00:09:41,666 --> 00:09:45,499
<i>joined now by Triperot Mayor,
Wayne John John-John.</i>

161
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:49,124
<i>Mayor John-John, do we know
who's behind this savage attack?</i>

162
00:09:49,125 --> 00:09:50,249
<i>Thank you, Beverly.</i>

163
00:09:50,250 --> 00:09:52,540
<i>Number one, as always,</i>

164
00:09:52,541 --> 00:09:54,290
<i>our thoughts and prayers</i>

165
00:09:54,291 --> 00:09:57,749
<i>are with those affected
by this meat-astrophe.</i>

166
00:09:57,750 --> 00:10:00,915
<i>Number two, election day is coming up,</i>

167
00:10:00,916 --> 00:10:05,832
<i>so remember, a vote for John-John
is a vote for fun-fun.</i>

168
00:10:05,833 --> 00:10:07,082
<i>And number three,</i>

169
00:10:07,083 --> 00:10:10,874
<i>those evildoers
may have blown up our water tower,</i>

170
00:10:10,875 --> 00:10:15,875
<i>but they can never blow up
the spirit of this great city.</i>

171
00:10:16,458 --> 00:10:18,165
How can he blame us?

172
00:10:18,166 --> 00:10:21,624
Any reasonable person
would've done exactly the same thing

173
00:10:21,625 --> 00:10:24,332
if they'd had their fun park shut down.

174
00:10:24,333 --> 00:10:27,165
If that bum don't like us
blowing up that water tower,

175
00:10:27,166 --> 00:10:29,875
I say we blow up his butt.

176
00:10:35,083 --> 00:10:37,665
<i>The mayor's butt would eventually explode.</i>

177
00:10:37,666 --> 00:10:40,207
<i>However, we can talk about that later.</i>

178
00:10:40,208 --> 00:10:46,290
<i>For now, the Twits' trick was having
very real consequences for our heroes.</i>

179
00:10:46,291 --> 00:10:48,790
I'm so happy you're going to be my parents

180
00:10:48,791 --> 00:10:52,540
because all I've ever wanted
is... is to find a family.

181
00:10:52,541 --> 00:10:53,915
Oh, boy.

182
00:10:53,916 --> 00:10:58,290
You're not gonna find a cuter child
in the tristate area, Mr. and Mrs. Klurb.

183
00:10:58,291 --> 00:10:59,541
That's a promise.

184
00:11:01,541 --> 00:11:03,332
Here's the deal, friend.

185
00:11:03,333 --> 00:11:08,124
We've reconsidered, actually,
based on circumstances,

186
00:11:08,125 --> 00:11:11,707
and, uh, you know,
adopting this kid over here, you know,

187
00:11:11,708 --> 00:11:13,874
that's gonna be a no-go for us.

188
00:11:13,875 --> 00:11:16,707
Yeah, we've seen on the news
how certain parts of town

189
00:11:16,708 --> 00:11:20,208
are still finding high levels
of liquid hot dog meat in their pipes.

190
00:11:20,791 --> 00:11:24,665
And then we seen your kids here
drinking that toxic meat water.

191
00:11:24,666 --> 00:11:28,457
Breaks my heart to say it,
but we just don't have the money

192
00:11:28,458 --> 00:11:31,083
to care for a contaminated child.

193
00:11:33,958 --> 00:11:38,083
We've decided to take our business
to another orphanage.

194
00:11:38,583 --> 00:11:40,374
Sorry, bucko.

195
00:11:40,375 --> 00:11:45,207
It's okay, Bubsy, those folks
don't know what they're talking about.

196
00:11:45,208 --> 00:11:48,416
We'll find you a family yet,
I guarantee it.

197
00:11:58,125 --> 00:12:00,707
I'm never gonna get adopted, Beesh.

198
00:12:00,708 --> 00:12:02,165
Yes, you are.

199
00:12:02,166 --> 00:12:04,290
You just have to have hope.

200
00:12:04,291 --> 00:12:07,707
I mean, my dream
is to see my parents again.

201
00:12:07,708 --> 00:12:10,790
Even though I know
they're coming back for me,

202
00:12:10,791 --> 00:12:12,791
it's still hard to wait.

203
00:12:13,458 --> 00:12:17,957
But some incredible family
is gonna find you so soon.

204
00:12:17,958 --> 00:12:19,332
I can feel it.

205
00:12:19,333 --> 00:12:22,832
And until that happens, I got your back.

206
00:12:22,833 --> 00:12:24,374
And your nose.

207
00:12:24,375 --> 00:12:27,040
And your intestines!

208
00:12:27,041 --> 00:12:31,332
You always have everyone's back, Beesh.
And their nose, and their intestines.

209
00:12:31,333 --> 00:12:32,457
I try.

210
00:12:32,458 --> 00:12:34,500
But who takes care of you?

211
00:12:35,083 --> 00:12:37,332
I don't need anyone to take care of me.

212
00:12:37,333 --> 00:12:39,333
I'm 12. Almost.

213
00:12:40,250 --> 00:12:43,083
So, yeah. I'm fine.

214
00:12:45,416 --> 00:12:46,833
But you're not fine.

215
00:12:47,416 --> 00:12:49,666
And this city isn't fine. I just...

216
00:12:50,375 --> 00:12:54,540
I want people to not be
so terrible to each other all the time.

217
00:12:54,541 --> 00:12:55,874
So you know what?

218
00:12:55,875 --> 00:12:58,290
I'm not gonna sit here and wait around

219
00:12:58,291 --> 00:13:01,082
for someone else
to make the world less cruel. Uh-uh.

220
00:13:01,083 --> 00:13:03,165
I'm gonna go out there and follow clues

221
00:13:03,166 --> 00:13:05,790
and find whoever put the meat
in that water tower.

222
00:13:05,791 --> 00:13:08,957
And I am going to bring
those jerks to justice.

223
00:13:08,958 --> 00:13:12,082
Will you shut up?!

224
00:13:12,083 --> 00:13:14,624
We're trying to be quiet here!

225
00:13:14,625 --> 00:13:18,249
How am I supposed to steal
these chemical loos

226
00:13:18,250 --> 00:13:20,958
with all that honking, you baby diaper?

227
00:13:29,791 --> 00:13:32,790
Aren't those the people
from the Twitlandia ad, Beesh?

228
00:13:32,791 --> 00:13:34,790
That's gotta be who did it.

229
00:13:34,791 --> 00:13:38,582
Looks like you're gonna get to go
to Twitlandia after all. Come on.

230
00:13:38,583 --> 00:13:40,708
Whoo-hoo!

231
00:13:41,750 --> 00:13:44,707
I know we're trying
to capture criminals, Beesh,

232
00:13:44,708 --> 00:13:47,624
but I still wanna go on a roller coaster.

233
00:13:47,625 --> 00:13:49,875
There it is. There's the truck.

234
00:13:51,416 --> 00:13:54,166
How have the police not figured this out?

235
00:14:01,375 --> 00:14:02,290
Beesha?

236
00:14:02,291 --> 00:14:03,540
We'll be fine.

237
00:14:03,541 --> 00:14:04,666
Come on.

238
00:14:27,750 --> 00:14:30,957
Twitlandia looked way nicer
in the commercial.

239
00:14:30,958 --> 00:14:32,415
Yeah.

240
00:14:32,416 --> 00:14:35,374
It looks like a place
