524
00:30:03,625 --> 00:30:05,540
Oh, thank you, Mr. and Mrs. Twit!

525
00:30:05,541 --> 00:30:07,915
- A billion to you!
- I want a billion!

526
00:30:07,916 --> 00:30:11,833
- A billion for you! Billion! Billion!
- Whoo-hoo!

527
00:30:12,958 --> 00:30:15,540
Our Twitlandia dream is gonna come true.

528
00:30:15,541 --> 00:30:18,332
They love me. They really love me.

529
00:30:18,333 --> 00:30:20,540
- Let me get that for you, lass.
- Ooh!

530
00:30:20,541 --> 00:30:22,375
Whoa!

531
00:30:34,333 --> 00:30:37,749
Ugh. What is it
with these people and toilets?

532
00:30:37,750 --> 00:30:39,915
Maybe they have small bladders

533
00:30:39,916 --> 00:30:42,874
and have to go
in the middle of the night sometimes.

534
00:30:42,875 --> 00:30:43,833
Huh.

535
00:30:49,666 --> 00:30:50,582
Yoo-hoo!

536
00:30:50,583 --> 00:30:54,000
Our big celebration supper's
almost ready, Jimmy.

537
00:30:58,458 --> 00:31:00,083
Mm!

538
00:31:01,375 --> 00:31:05,124
It's a special new kind of spaghetti
for my special guy.

539
00:31:05,125 --> 00:31:08,165
Eat it up now while it's nice and hot.

540
00:31:08,166 --> 00:31:09,583
Hot, hot, hot, hot.

541
00:31:15,625 --> 00:31:17,707
Yeah, it... it's squishy

542
00:31:17,708 --> 00:31:20,999
with a... with a hint
of distinctly bitter flavor.

543
00:31:21,000 --> 00:31:24,083
You wanna know
why your spaghetti's squishy?

544
00:31:25,083 --> 00:31:25,915
Why?

545
00:31:25,916 --> 00:31:28,166
And why it has a bitter taste?

546
00:31:29,041 --> 00:31:30,082
Why?

547
00:31:30,083 --> 00:31:33,541
Because it's worms! You're eating worms!

548
00:31:37,250 --> 00:31:39,624
Okay.

549
00:31:39,625 --> 00:31:45,250
If I were a key,
I'd hide under a pillow, maybe?

550
00:31:47,250 --> 00:31:49,665
Voice Changer 30,000? What's this...

551
00:31:49,666 --> 00:31:52,708
<i>...thing do? Whoa, that's really weird.</i>

552
00:32:07,791 --> 00:32:09,666
Mm.

553
00:32:14,291 --> 00:32:15,582
Was that the Twits?

554
00:32:15,583 --> 00:32:18,707
It can't be.
They've gotta be in jail by now.

555
00:32:18,708 --> 00:32:19,957
It's...

556
00:32:19,958 --> 00:32:22,165
It's been a long day.

557
00:32:22,166 --> 00:32:23,957
I'm tired.

558
00:32:23,958 --> 00:32:26,166
Let's just... go to bed.

559
00:32:28,250 --> 00:32:30,708
What the...? What's happening?

560
00:32:31,708 --> 00:32:33,541
Oh no! Oh no!

561
00:32:39,750 --> 00:32:41,041
This is not good.

562
00:32:42,125 --> 00:32:43,082
They are home,

563
00:32:43,083 --> 00:32:45,916
and now they're gonna put us
in a pie and eat us.

564
00:32:58,625 --> 00:32:59,750
- Beesh.
- Duck!

565
00:33:08,041 --> 00:33:10,791
We're fine, Bubs. We're fine. We're okay.

566
00:33:48,916 --> 00:33:50,958
Ugh.

567
00:33:59,166 --> 00:34:00,375
The key.

568
00:34:09,416 --> 00:34:10,625
It's in his beard.

569
00:34:18,291 --> 00:34:19,125
Ew.

570
00:34:28,875 --> 00:34:31,291
Blech.

571
00:34:35,166 --> 00:34:37,457
What are you doing, woman?!

572
00:34:37,458 --> 00:34:39,416
Come on. Let's go.

573
00:34:42,333 --> 00:34:44,249
- Hey, what...
- It's them kids.

574
00:34:44,250 --> 00:34:45,375
Go, go, go!

575
00:34:46,583 --> 00:34:47,541
Oh!

576
00:34:48,041 --> 00:34:52,124
We got the key!

577
00:34:52,125 --> 00:34:53,790
- Oh my gosh, really?
- No way!

578
00:34:53,791 --> 00:34:55,707
You guys are my heroes!

579
00:34:55,708 --> 00:34:57,165
Come on. Come on.

580
00:34:57,166 --> 00:35:00,624
I'm gonna put you kids in a pie
and cook you both for supper!

581
