616
00:37:03,666 --> 00:37:06,124
No one's gonna die, Harold.

617
00:37:06,125 --> 00:37:07,415
Just nobody panic.

618
00:37:07,416 --> 00:37:09,749
But Harold told us to panic.

619
00:37:09,750 --> 00:37:11,832
- Tuna, Harold, get the blocks.
- Huh?

620
00:37:11,833 --> 00:37:14,165
Everybody else, cardboard and crayons now.

621
00:37:14,166 --> 00:37:15,375
You got it.

622
00:37:24,750 --> 00:37:26,250
Oh, boy.

623
00:37:27,750 --> 00:37:32,665
Uh, so, um, what exactly
can I help you with, Mr. and Mrs. Twit?

624
00:37:32,666 --> 00:37:35,124
Your no-good children
stole our Muggle-Wumps.

625
00:37:35,125 --> 00:37:37,124
Sorry, my who stole your what?

626
00:37:37,125 --> 00:37:41,082
The creatures whose tears
are the power source for our fun park.

627
00:37:41,083 --> 00:37:44,290
You know we can't run Twitlandia
without the Muggle-Wumps.

628
00:37:44,291 --> 00:37:47,457
Yeah, see, I'm hearing words
come out of your mouth,

629
00:37:47,458 --> 00:37:50,790
but I'm not comprehending
their... their meaning.

630
00:37:50,791 --> 00:37:55,124
If you won't hand over our Muggle-Wumps,
you're gonna have to pay us.

631
00:37:55,125 --> 00:37:59,124
Those animals is worth $1 billion.

632
00:37:59,125 --> 00:38:02,249
Oh, I'm a bit cash poor at the moment.

633
00:38:02,250 --> 00:38:04,957
Um, my investments
are primarily emotional.

634
00:38:04,958 --> 00:38:07,915
In that case,
give us some of your possessions.

635
00:38:07,916 --> 00:38:10,165
We'll take, mm,

636
00:38:10,166 --> 00:38:14,124
the shoes, the shirt,
the slacks, and... the watch.

637
00:38:14,125 --> 00:38:17,207
But this watch belonged to my late father.

638
00:38:17,208 --> 00:38:21,374
If he was late,
it mustn't have been a very good watch.

639
00:38:21,375 --> 00:38:22,375
Come on.

640
00:38:23,500 --> 00:38:25,707
Don't come back, or we'll take the briefs.

641
00:38:25,708 --> 00:38:27,458
Hey! And the sock!

642
00:38:28,500 --> 00:38:31,875
Well, glad I decided
to put on briefs this morning.

643
00:38:32,458 --> 00:38:35,000
<i>Rainbows are coming back in...</i>

644
00:38:36,166 --> 00:38:37,999
Oh, right back at you. Toot-toot!

645
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:39,875
- Get a job!
- Oh, jeez.

646
00:38:40,500 --> 00:38:42,999
Mr. Napkin got tricked
out of his pants again!

647
00:38:43,000 --> 00:38:47,250
