My parents are coming back for me.

691
00:42:08,708 --> 00:42:10,791
She thinks they're coming back!

692
00:42:13,166 --> 00:42:15,582
That's the funniest thing
I've heard in ages!

693
00:42:15,583 --> 00:42:21,124
Thing is, kid, I was abandoned
at the circus by my deadbeat parents.

694
00:42:21,125 --> 00:42:25,124
And mine abandoned me at a bowling alley.

695
00:42:25,125 --> 00:42:29,332
So you see, you really is just like us.

696
00:42:29,333 --> 00:42:32,999
Only smaller and less intelligent.

697
00:42:33,000 --> 00:42:35,999
- I will never be like you.
- Oh...

698
00:42:36,000 --> 00:42:40,249
I am never giving up the Muggle-Wumps,
and this orphanage is owned by Triperot.

699
00:42:40,250 --> 00:42:42,957
So unless you're the stinking mayor,

700
00:42:42,958 --> 00:42:45,416
I suggest you keep out!

701
00:42:53,833 --> 00:42:57,915
Here she is, the greatest dancer
in the history of Loompaland,

702
00:42:57,916 --> 00:43:00,083
Mandy Muggle-Wump!

703
00:43:05,958 --> 00:43:07,665
Our first night of freedom.

704
00:43:07,666 --> 00:43:10,957
I am so snozzing happy, I could just...

705
00:43:10,958 --> 00:43:12,416
Wa-hoo!

706
00:43:14,375 --> 00:43:15,333
Yes!

707
00:43:17,250 --> 00:43:18,415
The heck?

708
00:43:18,416 --> 00:43:20,332
Oh, do humans not glow?

709
00:43:20,333 --> 00:43:23,624
I mean, obviously you don't
when your tears are being harvested

710
00:43:23,625 --> 00:43:26,249
to power an amusement park
because, like, duh.

711
00:43:26,250 --> 00:43:28,415
But otherwise, you glow, right?

712
00:43:28,416 --> 00:43:30,082
I don't think I glow.

713
00:43:30,083 --> 00:43:32,582
Huh. Well, learn something new every day.

714
00:43:32,583 --> 00:43:33,958
Mama!

715
00:43:36,875 --> 00:43:38,083
Whee!

716
00:43:42,083 --> 00:43:44,208
Go, Harold! Go, Harold!

717
00:43:52,666 --> 00:43:54,833
Don't let the Twits get into your head.

718
00:43:55,458 --> 00:43:57,749
You got us out of that cage, Beesha.

719
00:43:57,750 --> 00:43:58,958
We won.

720
00:44:01,625 --> 00:44:02,458
Yeah!

721
00:44:03,916 --> 00:44:05,582
Beesha! We're free!

722
00:44:05,583 --> 00:44:07,165
Come on, dance with me!

723
00:44:07,166 --> 00:44:09,375
We're free!

724
00:44:11,458 --> 00:44:14,915
<i>While the children
and the Muggle-Wumps celebrated,</i>

725
00:44:14,916 --> 00:44:16,999
<i>the Twits schemed,</i>

726
00:44:17,000 --> 00:44:19,957
<i>cooking up a trick that,
in the coming days,</i>

727
00:44:19,958 --> 00:44:23,249
<i>would have truly explosive consequences</i>

728
00:44:23,250 --> 00:44:27,250
<i>for the city of Triperot
and for our heroes.</i>

729
00:44:28,583 --> 00:44:30,874
<i>- My detractors say I'm soft on crime.</i>
- Ooh!

730
00:44:30,875 --> 00:44:32,665
<i>They say I tanked the economy.</i>

731
00:44:32,666 --> 00:44:35,374
<i>Well, I say I'm running unopposed.</i>

732
00:44:35,375 --> 00:44:37,082
<i>So when you vote for mayor,</i>

733
00:44:37,083 --> 00:44:40,500
<i>just remember, a vote for John-John
is a vote for fun-fun.</i>

734
00:44:41,500 --> 00:44:44,290
Mary! Get in here right now!

735
00:44:44,291 --> 00:44:46,499
Please hurry!

736
00:44:46,500 --> 00:44:49,457
Look, they've got this window
that looks into a world

737
00:44:49,458 --> 00:44:52,832
where a little tiny man
gets handed a stick by another man

