00:58:12,750 --> 00:58:16,083
Ready, aim, fire!

983
00:58:19,875 --> 00:58:21,166
Fire!

984
00:58:22,583 --> 00:58:24,290
Snakes. Spiders. Dentists.

985
00:58:24,291 --> 00:58:25,582
- Mimes.
- Creepy clowns.

986
00:58:25,583 --> 00:58:26,665
Vermicious Knids.

987
00:58:26,666 --> 00:58:27,957
Bubblegum in your hair.

988
00:58:27,958 --> 00:58:30,124
Forgetting pants when you go to school.

989
00:58:30,125 --> 00:58:33,457
I'm just... I'm... I'm having anxiety
about my anxiety.

990
00:58:33,458 --> 00:58:37,958
You know what gives me anxiety, Marty?
The thought of going back in that cage.

991
00:58:57,291 --> 00:58:58,708
What in the...?

992
00:59:03,458 --> 00:59:06,125
- Thank you for your service!
- Whee!

993
00:59:07,416 --> 00:59:08,666
Whee!

994
00:59:26,500 --> 00:59:28,582
What on earth are these things?

995
00:59:28,583 --> 00:59:31,415
Get back here!
Nobody told you you could leave.

996
00:59:31,416 --> 00:59:32,707
Cowards!

997
00:59:32,708 --> 00:59:34,457
- Touchdown!
- Yes!

998
00:59:34,458 --> 00:59:35,915
Yes!

999
00:59:35,916 --> 00:59:36,999
Beesha!

1000
00:59:37,000 --> 00:59:38,208
What is it, Bub?

1001
00:59:42,125 --> 00:59:44,708
Mr. Napkin, don't let them in!

1002
00:59:45,541 --> 00:59:47,415
Get out of the way, Crapkin.

1003
00:59:47,416 --> 00:59:50,874
We know our Muggle-Wumps are here,
so let us in.

1004
00:59:50,875 --> 00:59:52,666
Let you in, huh?

1005
00:59:53,666 --> 00:59:55,000
Nah.

1006
00:59:56,750 --> 00:59:59,333
- I don't think we'll be doing that today.
- Hmm?

1007
01:00:16,083 --> 01:00:19,040
If you think you're getting
into this orphanage,

1008
01:00:19,041 --> 01:00:21,624
I say, not on my watch.

1009
01:00:21,625 --> 01:00:24,207
Mostly because you took my watch,

1010
01:00:24,208 --> 01:00:25,374
but anyhoo...

1011
01:00:25,375 --> 01:00:28,916
...not on my watch!

1012
01:00:34,541 --> 01:00:35,790
This ain't over.

1013
01:00:35,791 --> 01:00:37,666
Oh, I think it is.

1014
01:00:40,875 --> 01:00:42,540
We'll be back.

1015
01:00:42,541 --> 01:00:46,457
Whoo! Napkin for the Nap-win! Ah!

1016
01:00:46,458 --> 01:00:48,166
Wow, Mr. Napkin!

1017
01:00:50,833 --> 01:00:52,582
Mr. Napkin.

1018
01:00:52,583 --> 01:00:55,374
Did you lick the Sweet-Toed Toad's toes?

1019
01:00:55,375 --> 01:00:57,999
I... I guess I did.

1020
01:00:58,000 --> 01:01:00,874
I mean, I'd never had a toad
talk to me before.

1021
01:01:00,875 --> 01:01:03,332
I heard him
and thought it sounded interesting,

1022
01:01:03,333 --> 01:01:05,457
so I... I licked the toes.

1023
01:01:05,458 --> 01:01:08,790
And as soon as I did,
I suddenly felt real crabby.

1024
01:01:08,791 --> 01:01:11,665
- And powerful.
- Kind of like the opposite of yourself?

1025
01:01:11,666 --> 01:01:13,999
Well, yeah, I guess that about sums it up.

1026
01:01:14,000 --> 01:01:15,249
That makes sense.

1027
01:01:15,250 --> 01:01:17,416
He's an Opposite Toad from Loompaland.

1028
01:01:19,083 --> 01:01:21,124
<i>Turmoil in Triperot tonight,</i>

1029
01:01:21,125 --> 01:01:23,999
<i>as former mayor Wayne John John-John</i>

1030
01:01:24,000 --> 01:01:27,624
<i>recovers from emergency
butt replacement surgery.</i>

1031
01:01:27,625 --> 01:01:31,040
<i>Meanwhile, Triperot's new mayors,
Credenza and Jim Twit,</i>

1032
01:01:31,041 --> 01:01:35,415
<i>declared war
on some local orphan children and lost.</i>

1033
01:01:35,416 --> 01:01:39,582
<i>The victorious youngsters have
one brave orphan to thank,</i>

1034
01:01:39,583 --> 01:01:40,832
<i>Beesha Balti.</i>

1035
01:01:40,833 --> 01:01:43,415
The Muggle-Wump family
is under my protection.

1036
01:01:43,416 --> 01:01:45,040
So as long as I'm here,

1037
01:01:45,041 --> 01:01:47,540
the Twits will never set foot
in this orphanage,

1038
01:01:47,541 --> 01:01:50,916
and Twitlandia will never ever open.

1039
01:01:55,375 --> 01:01:58,541
That little brat's ruining our lives!

1040
01:02:03,583 --> 01:02:05,957
What in God's name
are you doing down there?

1041
01:02:05,958 --> 01:02:07,999
I'm playing with me diarrhea.

1042
01:02:08,000 --> 01:02:11,082
You think squishing your face
around in diarrhea's

1043
01:02:11,083 --> 01:02:13,749
somehow gonna bring
them Muggle-Wumps back?

1044
01:02:13,750 --> 01:02:15,790
You know how that kid operates.

1045
01:02:15,791 --> 01:02:17,707
She's wily like a sea bass.

1046
01:02:17,708 --> 01:02:20,499
She ain't never gonna let us
get into that orphanage.

1047
01:02:20,500 --> 01:02:23,790
Oh, you poor, pointless, old wombat.

1048
01:02:23,791 --> 01:02:27,375
Who said anything about going in?

1049
01:02:36,291 --> 01:02:40,707
Come on. Enough cleaning, Beesha.
Everyone else is asleep up there.

1050
01:02:40,708 --> 01:02:43,249
I'm honestly not really tired.

1051
01:02:43,250 --> 01:02:45,499
So I might as well take the first watch.

1052
01:02:45,500 --> 01:02:49,665
All right, but if you wanna keep
those elbows, repeat after me.

1053
01:02:49,666 --> 01:02:52,582
"I will sound the alarm
if I see the Twits,

1054
01:02:52,583 --> 01:02:56,040
and no matter what,
I will not go it alone."

1055
01:02:56,041 --> 01:02:57,999
I won't go it alone,

1056
01:02:58,000 --> 01:03:02,457
and I promise, promise, promise
I'll sound the alarm if I see them.

1057
01:03:02,458 --> 01:03:03,707
My heart is a door,

1058
01:03:03,708 --> 01:03:07,083
and my love goes out
into the world through that heart door.

1059
01:03:07,875 --> 01:03:09,457
Uh, what?

1060
01:03:09,458 --> 01:03:12,290
Oh, no, you're supposed
to repeat after me too.

1061
01:03:12,291 --> 01:03:14,040
I think I'm good.

1062
01:03:14,041 --> 01:03:16,165
Okay, well maybe just do this.

1063
01:03:16,166 --> 01:03:19,082
My heart door will stay open

1064
01:03:19,083 --> 01:03:22,208
to accept the love of others.

1065
01:03:24,916 --> 01:03:27,915
My heart door will stay open
to accept the love of others.

1066
01:03:27,916 --> 01:03:30,666
Because I deserve to be loved.

1067
01:03:41,375 --> 01:03:45,541
Because I... deserve to be loved.

1068
01:04:06,541 --> 01:04:07,374
Hello?

1069
01:04:07,375 --> 01:04:09,374
<i>Beesha, you won't believe it!</i>

1070
01:04:09,375 --> 01:04:11,582
Mr. Napkin? Uh, where are you?

1071
01:04:11,583 --> 01:04:13,165
<i>I'm with your parents.</i>

1072
01:04:13,166 --> 01:04:14,332
Uh...

1073
01:04:14,333 --> 01:04:16,832
- What?
<i>- Yeah, they saw you on the news.</i>

1074
01:04:16,833 --> 01:04:18,875
<i>They really wanna meet you.</i>

1075
01:04:19,791 --> 01:04:21,415
<i>I'm with them right now,</i>

1076
01:04:21,416 --> 01:04:24,375
<i>out at the bowling alley
on Tripecrest Road.</i>

1077
01:04:25,750 --> 01:04:28,583
<i>They seem like real decent folks, Beesha.</i>

1078
01:04:29,333 --> 01:04:30,333
<i>They really do.</i>

1079
01:04:36,208 --> 01:04:40,124
Don't, Beesha! Don't!
It's a trick, isn't it?

1080
01:04:40,125 --> 01:04:42,749
Tell me she's not falling for this, Mum.

1081
01:04:42,750 --> 01:04:44,582
I can't tell you that.

1082
01:04:44,583 --> 01:04:49,249
Remember, when you desperately
want something to be true...

1083
01:04:49,250 --> 01:04:52,166
It's easy to convince yourself that it is,

1084
01:04:53,000 --> 01:04:54,291
even if it's not.

1085
01:04:56,208 --> 01:04:57,707
Mom! Dad!

1086
01:04:57,708 --> 01:04:58,916
I'm here!

1087
01:04:59,416 --> 01:05:01,416
I can't believe you came back.

1088
01:05:07,083 --> 01:05:11,208
I<i>can't</i> believe you came back.

1089
01:05:13,375 --> 01:05:15,125
They're never coming back.

1090
01:05:25,333 --> 01:05:27,499
I can't believe she fell for it.

1091
01:05:27,500 --> 01:05:31,290
The Voice Changer 30,000...
<i>...comes through again.</i>

1092
01:05:31,291 --> 01:05:34,415
<i>I knew if you heard
that potato-brained Napkin's voice,</i>

1093
01:05:34,416 --> 01:05:35,832
<i>you'd believe anything.</i>

1094
01:05:35,833 --> 01:05:39,707
And you did.

1095
01:05:39,708 --> 01:05:42,625
Now let's go get our Muggle-Wumps.

1096
01:05:51,541 --> 01:05:54,250
No! No, no, no!

1097
01:05:59,458 --> 01:06:00,500
Hmm.

1098
01:06:20,958 --> 01:06:23,165
Uh, what's happening?

1099
01:06:23,166 --> 01:06:26,165
Is this an earthquake? Where's Beesha?

1100
01:06:26,166 --> 01:06:27,707
Come on, Twitheads!

1101
01:06:27,708 --> 01:06:32,832
With the proper mob mentality,
we can move mountains!

1102
01:06:32,833 --> 01:06:35,874
Heave-ho now! Heave-ho!

1103
01:06:35,875 --> 01:06:37,750
Heave-ho!

1104
01:06:38,791 --> 01:06:40,208
Heave-ho!

1105
01:06:44,458 --> 01:06:45,624
Ho!

1106
01:06:45,625 --> 01:06:47,083
Heave-ho!

1107
01:06:50,750 --> 01:06:52,041
It's glued shut!

1108
01:06:52,541 --> 01:06:55,166
So is this one. We're trapped!

1109
01:06:58,833 --> 01:07:00,750
Heave-ho!

1110
01:07:04,541 --> 01:07:06,708
Mama!

1111
01:07:09,291 --> 01:07:10,500
Help! Help!

1112
01:07:20,708 --> 01:07:22,666
Heave-ho!

1113
01:07:33,958 --> 01:07:35,875
Hey! Wait for me!

1114
01:07:40,916 --> 01:07:42,208
Yee-haw!

1115
01:07:45,708 --> 01:07:47,583
Next stop, Twitlandia!

1116
01:07:55,000 --> 01:07:57,207
Oh, no, no, no, no, no!

1117
01:07:57,208 --> 01:07:59,208
What happened? How?

1118
01:08:00,916 --> 01:08:03,083
Mrs. M? Bubsy?

1119
01:08:04,500 --> 01:08:05,415
Mr. Napkin?

1120
01:08:05,416 --> 01:08:07,458
Is anyone here?

1121
01:08:12,000 --> 01:08:13,083
What did I do?

1122
01:08:14,375 --> 01:08:15,874
What did I do?

1123
01:08:15,875 --> 01:08:18,249
How could you fall for that, you idiot?

1124
01:08:18,250 --> 01:08:20,124
Idiot. Idiot.

1125
01:08:20,125 --> 01:08:23,875
I hate them. I hate the Twits so much!

1126
01:08:28,041 --> 01:08:30,124
Ow.

1127
01:08:30,125 --> 01:08:32,458
What... What happened? How was...?

1128
01:08:35,625 --> 01:08:37,415
The Twits stole the orphanage.

1129
01:08:37,416 --> 01:08:41,499
I tried to stop them,
but a woman kicked me with denim boots.

1130
01:08:41,500 --> 01:08:43,165
Didn't even break her stride.

1131
01:08:43,166 --> 01:08:45,457
I grabbed hold of her denim boot.

1132
01:08:45,458 --> 01:08:47,915
She shook me once, tried to stomp on me.

1133
01:08:47,916 --> 01:08:49,416
Oh, the shame.

1134
01:08:50,166 --> 01:08:52,290
I got kicked by a denim boot.

1135
01:08:52,291 --> 01:08:54,415
This is all my fault.

1136
01:08:54,416 --> 01:08:58,332
I was supposed to be on watch,
but I abandoned everyone because...

1137
01:08:58,333 --> 01:09:00,457
I am such an idiot!

1138
01:09:00,458 --> 01:09:03,165
Thinking my parents
would actually come back for me.

1139
01:09:03,166 --> 01:09:04,208
Ow!

1140
01:09:05,208 --> 01:09:07,583
How is your tongue this...?

1141
01:09:08,333 --> 01:09:11,040
You must've licked my toes
without me knowing

1142
01:09:11,041 --> 01:09:13,790
'cause you're talking opposite right now.

1143
01:09:13,791 --> 01:09:17,124
Get it together, kid.
Your family needs you.

1144
01:09:17,125 --> 01:09:18,540
What family?

1145
01:09:18,541 --> 01:09:20,833
Isn't it obvious I don't have a fam...?

1146
01:09:22,583 --> 01:09:23,832
Hold on a minute!

1147
01:09:23,833 --> 01:09:26,540
If you don't have a family,
what do you call Bubsy?

1148
01:09:26,541 --> 01:09:29,582
Or the Muggle-Wumps? Or me?

1149
01:09:29,583 --> 01:09:32,999
What do you call that bald guy
with the high-waisted slacks

1150
01:09:33,000 --> 01:09:34,999
who talks about his mom a lot?

1151
01:09:35,000 --> 01:09:36,000
Hmm?

1152
01:09:36,583 --> 01:09:38,457
I call him Mr. Napkin.

1153
01:09:38,458 --> 01:09:41,707
You call him Mr. Napkin.

1154
01:09:41,708 --> 01:09:45,415
The way I see it,
family isn't just who you're related to.

1155
01:09:45,416 --> 01:09:49,540
It's who you care about,
and who cares about you,

1156
01:09:49,541 --> 01:09:53,916
and treats you with love
and kindness and empathy.

1157
01:09:55,250 --> 01:09:56,458
You're right.

1158
01:09:57,041 --> 01:09:58,790
The Twits hurt our family.

1159
01:09:58,791 --> 01:10:01,416
Now it's time to hurt them.

1160
01:10:02,000 --> 01:10:05,290
<i>Fun and excitement had a baby</i>

1161
01:10:05,291 --> 01:10:08,165
<i>And they called it Twitlandia</i>

1162
01:10:08,166 --> 01:10:10,124
Welcome, Twitheads,

1163
01:10:10,125 --> 01:10:13,040
to the re-grand opening of Twitlandia!

1164
01:10:13,041 --> 01:10:16,582
We are bigger and better than ever!

1165
01:10:16,583 --> 01:10:18,874
<i>Bigger and better</i>

1166
01:10:18,875 --> 01:10:22,415
Now you can spend the night,
and all your money,

1167
01:10:22,416 --> 01:10:25,457
at the Twitlandia Luxury Motel & Spa.

1168
01:10:25,458 --> 01:10:29,332
And after you have
a slice of my famous bird pie,

1169
01:10:29,333 --> 01:10:32,915
feel free to use our complimentary Napkin.

1170
01:10:32,916 --> 01:10:33,915
Oh, jeez.

1171
01:10:33,916 --> 01:10:36,249
Most importantly, thanks to you,

1172
01:10:36,250 --> 01:10:38,999
our Muggle-Wumps is back!

1173
01:10:39,000 --> 01:10:41,624
<i>Fun and excitement had a baby</i>

1174
01:10:41,625 --> 01:10:44,415
<i>They called it Twitlandia</i>

1175
01:10:44,416 --> 01:10:46,665
<i>Fun and excitement had a baby</i>

1176
01:10:46,666 --> 01:10:51,332
<i>And they called it Twitlandia</i>

1177
01:10:51,333 --> 01:10:52,749
Horvis Dungle!

1178
01:10:52,750 --> 01:10:57,790
Now, friends, Twitlandia is a fun park
that puts family values first,

1179
01:10:57,791 --> 01:11:02,207
which is why we want to introduce you
to someone very special.

1180
01:11:02,208 --> 01:11:06,125
Our precious little son, Butt Cheek Twit.

1181
01:11:07,916 --> 01:11:09,583
Aw.

1182
01:11:13,166 --> 01:11:15,707
Hello there. My name is Bubsy Twit...

1183
01:11:15,708 --> 01:11:17,165
Butt Cheek.

1184
01:11:17,166 --> 01:11:18,582
- My name is...
- Ah!

1185
01:11:18,583 --> 01:11:20,165
Butt Cheek Twit,

1186
01:11:20,166 --> 01:11:23,540
and all I ever wanted
was to find a family.

1187
01:11:23,541 --> 01:11:28,332
And now, I have one,
since Meemaw and Peepaw Twit adopted me

1188
01:11:28,333 --> 01:11:31,000
and all of my brothers and sisters.

1189
01:11:33,458 --> 01:11:34,999
That's right, folks.

1190
01:11:35,000 --> 01:11:39,082
We adapted a whole orphan-anage
full of youngsters.

1191
01:11:39,083 --> 01:11:44,832
Just to bring you the Twit Family
Memorial Song and Dance Extravaganza!

1192
01:11:44,833 --> 01:11:47,916
Hey! Hey!

1193
01:11:56,083 --> 01:11:57,499
Oh, Jim!

1194
01:11:57,500 --> 01:11:59,999
All our dreams are coming true.

1195
01:12:00,000 --> 01:12:01,582
I know it, woman.

1196
01:12:01,583 --> 01:12:04,625
Nothing could possibly
ruin this moment now.

1197
01:12:05,958 --> 01:12:07,375
Ha!

1198
01:12:37,291 --> 01:12:38,375
Ugh.

1199
01:12:44,500 --> 01:12:45,875
Bubs!

1200
01:12:47,291 --> 01:12:49,457
I'm so sorry I left you.

1201
01:12:49,458 --> 01:12:51,583
Hey, get that girl.

1202
01:12:52,666 --> 01:12:55,040
So I can give her a tender embrace.

1203
01:12:55,041 --> 01:12:57,832
Oh, what a wonderful child she is.

1204
01:12:57,833 --> 01:12:58,832
Now, stop!

1205
01:12:58,833 --> 01:13:02,415
You're tickling my whiskers,
you little whisker-tickler.

1206
01:13:02,416 --> 01:13:04,082
Oh!

1207
01:13:04,083 --> 01:13:06,124
- Are you looking for this?
- Uh...

1208
01:13:06,125 --> 01:13:08,624
Oh, bless her heart.

1209
01:13:08,625 --> 01:13:11,540
I think she wants to free
the Muggle-Wumps, Jim.

1210
01:13:11,541 --> 01:13:14,374
Oh? I would hope so.

1211
01:13:14,375 --> 01:13:16,375
It's the right thing to do.

1212
01:13:16,958 --> 01:13:19,332
Go free, you precious creatures.

1213
01:13:19,333 --> 01:13:20,540
Go free!

1214
01:13:20,541 --> 01:13:21,999
Thank you very much.

1215
01:13:22,000 --> 01:13:25,540
It feels so good to be good,
don't it, James?

1216
01:13:25,541 --> 01:13:29,040
It do feel good, like a summer breeze.

1217
01:13:29,041 --> 01:13:30,958
Ooh!

1218
01:13:35,125 --> 01:13:39,333
Didn't they say we need
those Muggle-Wumps to save the town?

1219
01:13:40,250 --> 01:13:42,916
Come on, let's go. Everyone hurry.

1220
01:13:43,750 --> 01:13:46,374
I kind of like having a beard.

1221
01:13:46,375 --> 01:13:48,541
Get a hold of yourself, Harold!

1222
01:13:49,791 --> 01:13:52,540
Stop! We're not leaving yet.

1223
01:13:52,541 --> 01:13:54,750
Beesha, what are you doing?

1224
01:13:55,500 --> 01:13:58,707
We're free.
There's nothing more for us to do here.

1225
01:13:58,708 --> 01:14:00,207
You're wrong, Mrs. M.

1226
01:14:00,208 --> 01:14:02,582
The effects of the toad's toes
will wear off,

1227
01:14:02,583 --> 01:14:04,833
and the Twits will go back to being twits.

1228
01:14:05,416 --> 01:14:07,124
You know better than anyone

1229
01:14:07,125 --> 01:14:09,790
that they will keep
coming after your family,

1230
01:14:09,791 --> 01:14:13,832
and hurting people, and hurting people,
and nothing will change.

1231
01:14:13,833 --> 01:14:17,165
We have to give them
a taste of their own medicine,

1232
01:14:17,166 --> 01:14:19,541
with a trick to end all tricks.

1233
01:14:20,250 --> 01:14:22,166
But I can't do it alone.

1234
01:14:23,166 --> 01:14:24,541
So who's with me?

1235
01:14:31,000 --> 01:14:32,790
Beg pardon, Mayor and Mayor Twit,

1236
01:14:32,791 --> 01:14:36,540
but you told us
if we gave you $1,000 it'd save Triperot

1237
01:14:36,541 --> 01:14:38,707
and make us billionaires
when the park opened.

1238
01:14:38,708 --> 01:14:42,540
Ah, the billionaire thing
and pretending we cared about Triperot.

1239
01:14:42,541 --> 01:14:44,291
Huh?

1240
01:14:44,875 --> 01:14:46,249
That was all a lie.

1241
01:14:46,250 --> 01:14:49,999
We spent all your money
on fake beards and fireworks.

1242
01:14:50,000 --> 01:14:51,124
For pity's sake.

1243
01:14:51,125 --> 01:14:53,540
You people gave us hope.

1244
01:14:53,541 --> 01:14:55,957
And you gave us everything
we ever dreamed of.

1245
01:14:55,958 --> 01:14:59,790
But seeing as how we got it
by lying and cheating and hurting you,

1246
01:14:59,791 --> 01:15:02,624
I... I don't like the woman I've become.

1247
01:15:02,625 --> 01:15:04,790
I'm ashamed of myself.

1248
01:15:04,791 --> 01:15:07,207
I don't like the man I've become.

1249
01:15:07,208 --> 01:15:09,208
I'm so sorry!

1250
01:15:11,458 --> 01:15:13,749
Well, "sorry" just ain't gonna cut it.

1251
01:15:13,750 --> 01:15:16,707
No way. I just put a down payment
on a new marimba.

1252
01:15:16,708 --> 01:15:18,957
You lied to us.

1253
01:15:18,958 --> 01:15:20,457
We trusted you!

1254
01:15:20,458 --> 01:15:24,457
Oh, James, we have taken everything
from these poor people.

1255
01:15:24,458 --> 01:15:26,540
There's only one thing to do.

1256
01:15:26,541 --> 01:15:29,749
Take everything from ourselves.

1257
01:15:29,750 --> 01:15:32,207
Friends, we've heard your concerns.

1258
01:15:32,208 --> 01:15:34,832
We've got a solution.

1259
01:15:34,833 --> 01:15:36,582
We're gonna blow up Twitlandia.

1260
01:15:36,583 --> 01:15:37,832
They're gonna what?!

1261
01:15:37,833 --> 01:15:39,499
Blow up what?

1262
01:15:39,500 --> 01:15:41,249
They're gonna blow it up?

1263
01:15:41,250 --> 01:15:44,875
- You mean right here where we're standing?
- These people are nuts.

1264
01:15:55,833 --> 01:15:59,665
You know, I'm starting to think
we should've listened to our daughter

1265
01:15:59,666 --> 01:16:03,665
instead of the two strangers
we saw getting arrested on the news.

1266
01:16:03,666 --> 01:16:06,875
I'm also thinking that also as well.

1267
01:16:16,625 --> 01:16:20,875
Oh, I love fireworks, James.

1268
01:16:33,333 --> 01:16:35,499
What happened to our fun park?

1269
01:16:35,500 --> 01:16:39,415
I have no idea,
but I'm certain it's your fault.

1270
01:16:39,416 --> 01:16:42,666
Where on earth is our Muggle-Wumps?

1271
01:16:43,666 --> 01:16:46,874
There goes the lady one.

1272
01:16:46,875 --> 01:16:47,958
Get her.

1273
01:16:53,250 --> 01:16:56,499
The Twits are coming!
The Twits are coming!

1274
01:16:56,500 --> 01:17:00,207
Go, go! More Hugtight glue on the floor.
Yeah, right there.

1275
01:17:00,208 --> 01:17:01,665
Come on, now.

1276
01:17:01,666 --> 01:17:05,332
All we wanna do is lock you in a cage
for the rest of your life,

1277
01:17:05,333 --> 01:17:06,707
and maybe eat you.

1278
01:17:06,708 --> 01:17:09,582
That little beast
is going inside our house.

1279
01:17:09,583 --> 01:17:11,291
Well, hurry up.

1280
01:17:15,541 --> 01:17:16,749
Whoo!

1281
01:17:16,750 --> 01:17:18,083
Come on, get in!

1282
01:17:25,291 --> 01:17:27,125
It went in there.

1283
01:17:30,250 --> 01:17:32,333
What is this?

1284
01:17:44,041 --> 01:17:46,457
What's happened? The floor is up there.

1285
01:17:46,458 --> 01:17:48,499
We're upside down.

1286
01:17:48,500 --> 01:17:50,374
We must be upside down.

1287
01:17:50,375 --> 01:17:53,541
I mean, we're standing on the ceiling,
looking at the floor.

1288
01:17:57,583 --> 01:18:00,707
Oh, help! I'm beginning to feel giddy.

1289
01:18:00,708 --> 01:18:02,707
I don't like this one little bit.

1290
01:18:02,708 --> 01:18:06,665
The blood's going to my head.
I feel like I'm gonna die!

1291
01:18:06,666 --> 01:18:10,332
How do I... Oh, I've got it! I've got it!
We stand on our heads!

1292
01:18:10,333 --> 01:18:11,624
What are you saying?

1293
01:18:11,625 --> 01:18:14,625
Stand on your head,
and then we'll be the right way up.

1294
01:18:18,833 --> 01:18:20,291
- Whoa.
- That's better.

1295
01:18:21,291 --> 01:18:23,332
Oh...

1296
01:18:23,333 --> 01:18:24,915
I'm glued.

1297
01:18:24,916 --> 01:18:28,250
It's Hugtight Sticky Glue.

1298
01:18:46,208 --> 01:18:47,832
We've been tricked.

1299
01:18:47,833 --> 01:18:50,624
You beastly little brats.

1300
01:18:50,625 --> 01:18:52,707
You cut us down this instant, or...

1301
01:18:52,708 --> 01:18:55,625
Or what? You'll cook us in a pie?

1302
01:18:56,750 --> 01:18:58,540
No, you won't.

1303
01:18:58,541 --> 01:19:01,999
You're never cooking another pie
because you're never getting free.

1304
01:19:02,000 --> 01:19:05,541
There's enough cruelty and hatred
without the two of you running around.

1305
01:19:06,541 --> 01:19:10,916
Trust me, the world will be
a much better place without you in it.

1306
01:19:23,041 --> 01:19:25,290
Oh! Cut it out.

1307
01:19:25,291 --> 01:19:28,915
Please, somebody!
There's a grackle eating my face!

1308
01:19:28,916 --> 01:19:31,540
Help! I have to go potty.

1309
01:19:31,541 --> 01:19:35,291
- Down with the Twits! Whoo-hoo!
- Help!

1310
01:19:40,000 --> 01:19:42,541
Take that, you dang rabbit.

1311
01:19:46,041 --> 01:19:49,457
What do you really think
will happen to the Twits?

1312
01:19:49,458 --> 01:19:51,541
Who gives a rip?

1313
01:19:52,833 --> 01:19:54,708
I know what'll happen.

1314
01:19:57,041 --> 01:20:01,457
They're gonna get the Dreaded Shrinks.

1315
01:20:01,458 --> 01:20:05,082
<i>That's what happens
if you stand on your head long enough.</i>

1316
01:20:05,083 --> 01:20:08,541
<i>First, their heads
will shrink into their necks.</i>

1317
01:20:09,875 --> 01:20:11,040
I'm shrinking!

1318
01:20:11,041 --> 01:20:14,708
Somebody save me!
I'm getting the Dreaded Shrinks!

1319
01:20:16,416 --> 01:20:19,625
<i>Then their necks
will shrink into their bodies.</i>

1320
01:20:21,291 --> 01:20:25,207
<i>Then their bodies
will shrink into their legs.</i>

1321
01:20:25,208 --> 01:20:28,624
<i>Then their legs
will shrink into their feet,</i>

1322
01:20:28,625 --> 01:20:31,790
<i>until there's nothing left
in this whole world</i>

1323
01:20:31,791 --> 01:20:33,750
<i>of Mr. and Mrs. Twit.</i>

1324
01:20:41,000 --> 01:20:44,040
Do you really think
that's gonna happen, Bubsy?

1325
01:20:44,041 --> 01:20:45,624
I hope it does.

1326
01:20:45,625 --> 01:20:50,041
What do you think, Mrs. M?
Think they'll melt into a puddle of goo?

1327
01:20:51,791 --> 01:20:53,416
Sorry, what's that?

1328
01:21:05,208 --> 01:21:06,041
Huh?

1329
01:21:16,041 --> 01:21:18,582
I can't understand
the Muggle-Wumps, Beesha.

1330
01:21:18,583 --> 01:21:19,708
Can you?

1331
01:21:20,958 --> 01:21:22,750
Um, Mrs. M?

1332
01:21:23,666 --> 01:21:25,832
What's happening?

1333
01:21:25,833 --> 01:21:29,666
Why can't I understand you?
Why can't I understand you?

1334
01:21:31,833 --> 01:21:35,583
Please, no. No, I need you.
I... I need you!

1335
01:21:45,250 --> 01:21:48,082
<i>Just as children
with a deep sense of empathy</i>

1336
01:21:48,083 --> 01:21:50,082
<i>can understand animals,</i>

1337
01:21:50,083 --> 01:21:52,541
<i>children without it can't.</i>

1338
01:21:53,875 --> 01:21:55,666
<i>It's as simple as that.</i>

1339
01:22:02,250 --> 01:22:05,208
You take all the good out of life.

1340
01:22:06,458 --> 01:22:09,041
And you're the worst person I've ever met.

1341
01:22:11,125 --> 01:22:16,500
<i>Hating you is easy
'Cause you're horrible</i>

1342
01:23:05,791 --> 01:23:08,541
What on earth
are you gribbly little grubs doing here?

1343
01:23:10,166 --> 01:23:15,165
We felt bad about the idea of you getting
the Dreaded Shrinks and, you know,

1344
01:23:15,166 --> 01:23:16,665
dying a horrible death.

1345
01:23:16,666 --> 01:23:18,291
So we came back to save you.

1346
01:23:19,416 --> 01:23:20,291
You did?

1347
01:23:21,500 --> 01:23:22,875
Sure did.

1348
01:23:23,708 --> 01:23:25,500
Hate is...

1349
01:23:26,791 --> 01:23:27,791
so easy.

1350
01:23:28,541 --> 01:23:30,832
You hate me, I hate you. Yay!

1351
01:23:30,833 --> 01:23:32,957
Now we're enemies for life,

1352
01:23:32,958 --> 01:23:38,707
and I never have to think about the fact
that you're both human beings.

1353
01:23:38,708 --> 01:23:42,540
Never have to wonder
how badly you must've suffered

1354
01:23:42,541 --> 01:23:44,666
to become this mean.

1355
01:23:45,166 --> 01:23:48,541
Or imagine what my parents
went through when they left me.

1356
01:23:50,500 --> 01:23:51,582
Hate's easy.

1357
01:23:51,583 --> 01:23:53,957
But it'll eat you up inside

1358
01:23:53,958 --> 01:23:57,915
until all that's left
is an angry little twit.

1359
01:23:57,916 --> 01:24:01,040
I don't wanna live in a world
where hate wins.

1360
01:24:01,041 --> 01:24:04,041
So yeah, I forgive you.

1361
01:24:04,541 --> 01:24:05,541
You're free.

1362
01:24:11,041 --> 01:24:12,541
Well, thank you.

1363
01:24:13,541 --> 01:24:15,583
Yeah. Thanks.

1364
01:24:18,666 --> 01:24:21,665
Now get over here
so I can cook you both in a pie.

1365
01:24:21,666 --> 01:24:24,707
Get back here,
you terrible little turnips!

1366
01:24:24,708 --> 01:24:26,000
I'm hungry!

1367
01:24:40,166 --> 01:24:42,332
- Oh no.
- I was afraid this might happen.

1368
01:24:42,333 --> 01:24:43,750
It was worth a try!

1369
01:24:47,541 --> 01:24:48,957
Whoa!

1370
01:24:48,958 --> 01:24:50,125
Whoa, whoa, whoa!

1371
01:24:52,583 --> 01:24:54,041
Good job, family.

1372
01:25:01,500 --> 01:25:05,290
<i>- Is that how the story ends?
- Not quite.</i>

1373
01:25:05,291 --> 01:25:07,625
Boing! Boing! Boing!

1374
01:25:11,458 --> 01:25:13,624
So long, Mr. and Mrs. Twit.

1375
01:25:13,625 --> 01:25:16,583
We'll be taking back our orphanage now.

1376
01:25:20,750 --> 01:25:23,249
- Well, that was unexpected.
- Yes.

1377
01:25:23,250 --> 01:25:27,999
And after Mr. Napkin returned
the orphanage to its rightful location,

1378
01:25:28,000 --> 01:25:30,999
the Muggle-Wumps
sold the formula for their tears

1379
01:25:31,000 --> 01:25:33,833
to a multinational corporation

1380
01:25:34,333 --> 01:25:38,916
which used the tears to end
the world's dependence on fossil fuels.

1381
01:25:39,458 --> 01:25:43,415
With the windfall of cash,
the Muggle-Wumps bought the orphanage,

1382
01:25:43,416 --> 01:25:47,249
adopted Beesha, Bubsy,
and all of the other orphans,

1383
01:25:47,250 --> 01:25:50,958
and hired Mr. Napkin
as a part-time au pair.

1384
01:25:51,458 --> 01:25:56,290
For her part, Beesha was credited
with saving Triperot from the Twits.

1385
01:25:56,291 --> 01:26:00,957
And with her idea to refill Tripe Lake
with florbnorbles,

1386
01:26:00,958 --> 01:26:05,666
Triperot became the fun capital
of the world once more.

1387
01:26:06,208 --> 01:26:08,499
And they all lived happily ever after?

1388
01:26:08,500 --> 01:26:10,583
Something like that.

1389
01:26:11,208 --> 01:26:12,499
Now go to bed.

1390
01:26:12,500 --> 01:26:16,208
Oh, man. You've got to at least tell me
what happened to the Twits.

1391
01:26:17,583 --> 01:26:18,874
All right.

1392
01:26:18,875 --> 01:26:21,957
You might think that the Twits
would've learned a lesson,

1393
01:26:21,958 --> 01:26:24,874
but it's not enough
to just learn something.

1394
01:26:24,875 --> 01:26:31,165
You have to want to change,
and then make an effort to actually do so.

1395
01:26:31,166 --> 01:26:35,499
Something the Twits
were entirely unwilling to do.

1396
01:26:35,500 --> 01:26:38,540
This is the only way
to get rid of the side effects

1397
01:26:38,541 --> 01:26:41,374
of the Dreaded Shrinks, my angel.

1398
01:26:41,375 --> 01:26:43,499
Can you feel them stretching you?

1399
01:26:43,500 --> 01:26:46,290
I can. They're stretching me like mad.

1400
01:26:46,291 --> 01:26:48,582
Good. That means it's working.

1401
01:26:48,583 --> 01:26:51,082
Are you sure my feet are tied properly?

1402
01:26:51,083 --> 01:26:55,040
If them strings around my ankles break,
it'll be goodbye for me.

1403
01:26:55,041 --> 01:26:57,332
That's enough pull to take me to the moon.

1404
01:26:57,333 --> 01:26:59,332
What a ghastly thought.

1405
01:26:59,333 --> 01:27:02,125
Wouldn't want anything
like that to happen, dear me.

1406
01:27:03,125 --> 01:27:04,083
No.

1407
01:27:07,291 --> 01:27:11,041
I'll get you for this,
you grizzly old grunion!

1408
01:27:12,958 --> 01:27:14,332
Oi!

1409
01:27:14,333 --> 01:27:16,125
Whoa!

1410
01:27:21,625 --> 01:27:26,000
Whoo-hoo!

1411
01:27:28,416 --> 01:27:30,582
No more beard, Mum!

1412
01:27:30,583 --> 01:27:32,916
We're free! We're free from the beard!

1413
01:27:46,541 --> 01:27:50,957
<i>Tears are like magic</i>

1414
01:27:50,958 --> 01:27:55,999
<i>And laughing is fun</i>

1415
01:27:56,000 --> 01:28:00,957
<i>If you can have both of them</i>

1416
01:28:00,958 --> 01:28:05,166
<i>Why just have one?</i>

1417
01:28:05,916 --> 01:28:10,249
<i>Everything matters</i>

1418
01:28:10,250 --> 01:28:15,457
<i>And all things belong</i>

1419
01:28:15,458 --> 01:28:20,082
<i>Fear is the same place</i>

1420
01:28:20,083 --> 01:28:24,708
<i>That courage comes from</i>

1421
01:28:30,041 --> 01:28:34,332
<i>Family's not only</i>

1422
01:28:34,333 --> 01:28:39,665
<i>Who you're related to</i>

1423
01:28:39,666 --> 01:28:44,207
<i>It's who you care for</i>

1424
01:28:44,208 --> 01:28:48,416
<i>And who cares for you</i>

1425
01:28:49,000 --> 01:28:53,290
<i>It's easy to hate</i>

1426
01:28:53,291 --> 01:28:58,749
<i>What you don't understand</i>

1427
01:28:58,750 --> 01:29:02,999
<i>If we don't agree</i>

1428
01:29:03,000 --> 01:29:08,500
<i>Could you still take my hand?</i>

1429
01:29:09,000 --> 01:29:10,750
<i>Open the door</i>

1430
01:29:11,375 --> 01:29:13,041
<i>Look what we've done</i>

1431
01:29:13,750 --> 01:29:15,458
<i>Open your heart</i>

1432
01:29:16,125 --> 01:29:18,165
<i>How far we've come</i>

1433
01:29:18,166 --> 01:29:22,332
<i>Lessons in life</i>

1434
01:29:22,333 --> 01:29:27,832
<i>They are learned in reverse</i>

1435
01:29:27,833 --> 01:29:31,915
<i>My wisest friends</i>

1436
01:29:31,916 --> 01:29:37,083
<i>Talk completely backwards</i>

1437
01:29:37,666 --> 01:29:42,040
<i>Nothing is pointless</i>

1438
01:29:42,041 --> 01:29:47,124
<i>And nothing's too much</i>

1439
